# Reorganize Codebase to Follow Nuxt Directory Structure

The project is a Nuxt 4 Hospital Management System with a patient kiosk and admin dashboard. Currently, all code lives in `app/` with minimal structureвЂ”types are inline, the admin sidebar layout is embedded in a page file, and there are no proper Nuxt layouts. This plan reorganizes the codebase to follow Nuxt's recommended directory conventions.

## Current Structure

```
app/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ app.vue
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ app.config.ts
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ assets/css/main.css
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ components/AppLogo.vue
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ composables/useLanguage.ts, useQueueState.ts
в””в”Ђв”Ђ pages/
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ index.vue          (home/landing)
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ kiosk.vue           (patient queuing kiosk)
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ admin.vue           (acts as "layout" via nested routes)
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ admin/
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ index.vue       (redirect to queuing)
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ queuing.vue
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ documents.vue
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ assets.vue
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ hr.vue
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ waste.vue
```

