в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ kiosk.vue
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ admin.vue          (sets layout: 'admin', renders NuxtPage)
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ admin/
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ index.vue
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ queuing.vue
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ documents.vue
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ assets.vue
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ hr.vue
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ waste.vue
в””в”Ђв”Ђ types/
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ queue.ts
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ admin.ts
```

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The [admin.vue](file:///c:/Users/barra/OneDrive/Desktop/code/app-hms/app/pages/admin.vue) page currently acts as both a page and a layout (sidebar + content area with nested `<NuxtPage />`). The plan converts it to a proper Nuxt layout file (`layouts/admin.vue`), while keeping [pages/admin.vue](file:///c:/Users/barra/OneDrive/Desktop/code/app-hms/app/pages/admin.vue) as a thin wrapper. This preserves all routing behavior.

> [!NOTE]
> Nuxt auto-imports from `types/`, `composables/`, and `components/` directories, so most import statements will be handled automatically.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- No existing test framework in the project

### Manual Verification
1. Run `pnpm dev` вЂ” confirm no build/compile errors
2. Open browser at `http://localhost:3000` вЂ” verify the landing page renders with the two entry cards
3. Click "Patient Kiosk" вЂ” verify kiosk page loads with departments and queue panel
4. Select a department вЂ” verify ticket modal appears with printing animation
5. Click "Admin Dashboard" вЂ” verify redirect to `/admin/queuing` with sidebar layout
6. Click each sidebar module (Documents, Assets, HR, Waste) вЂ” verify each loads correctly
7. Verify queue state syncs between kiosk and admin (generate ticket on kiosk, see it in admin queuing)
